The subjects spent half an hour in an MRI scanner, and during this time they received 20 electrocutions in four consecutive parts, either on a religious subject or on a general picture.
Catholics reported that in the sight of the Virgin Mary, they felt "safe" as they were "cared for" and "required, filled with peace".
