When places filled with history and memories disappear, "it's like a friend of ours going away, an acquaintance with whom we shared our path and many experiences," says the director of Cinema Paradiso. The film, which was an Oscar award twenty years ago and the grand prize of the Cannes festival, tells the story of a small-town cinema in Iria, the yearning for a movie that may have been lost forever.
